+# PR 214 Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed. `build_policy_preview(...)` now normalizes `manual_review` to
+`human_review_required` before calling `build_preview_payload(...)`, and the
+fallback payload in `src/policy/preview.py` now retains both
+`approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when `preview_enabled=False`.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. The reopened fallback payload regression was
+fixed in the shared preview path, so there is no separate code change for this
+thread.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Marked obsolete. This comment points at an outdated diff hunk and suggests
+reviving legacy preview behavior on the current branch. I did not apply it.
+The current fix keeps the modern flow and does not add any legacy preview
+branch or `legacy_preview_hint`.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Fixed. Added a regression test in `tests/test_preview.py` that exercises
+`build_policy_preview(..., preview_enabled=False, approval_state="manual_review", ...)`
+and asserts that the fallback payload still reports
+`approval_state="human_review_required"` with
+`requires_human_review=True`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Fixed. Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` so the fallback example now matches
+the corrected payload, including `approval_state` and
+`requires_human_review`.
